<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:building" title="Key:building"> building</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:building%3Dsty" title="Tag:building=sty">sty</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sty" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Sty">sty</a> (pigsty, pig ark, pig-shed) is a a building for raising domestic pigs, usually found on farms.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Schweinehütten.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/a/ac/Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg/100px-Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg" width="100" height="64" srcset="/w/images/thumb/a/ac/Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg/150px-Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/a/ac/Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg/200px-Schweineh%C3%BCtten.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:building" title="Key:building"> building</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:building%3Dtransformer_tower" title="Tag:building=transformer tower">transformer_tower</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A transformer tower is a characteristic tall building comprising a distribution transformer and constructed to provide direct connection to a medium voltage overhead power line. Quite often the power line has since been undergrounded but it may still serve as a substation. See also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dsubstation" title="Tag:power=substation">substation</a></tt>.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:OesterSkovVejHad.jpg" class="image"><img alt="OesterSkovVejHad.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/57/OesterSkovVejHad.jpg/100px-OesterSkovVejHad.jpg" width="100" height="133" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/57/OesterSkovVejHad.jpg/150px-OesterSkovVejHad.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/57/OesterSkovVejHad.jpg/200px-OesterSkovVejHad.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:building:fireproof" title="Key:building:fireproof"> building:fireproof</a>
</td>
<td> yes/no
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a><a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Fire-resistance information.
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Craft">Craft</span></h3>
<p>A place producing or processing customised goods. See <a href="/wiki/Crafts" title="Crafts">Crafts</a> for more information.

</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Emergency">Emergency</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe the location of emergency facilities and equipment. See <a href="/wiki/Emergency" title="Emergency">Emergency</a> for more information on usage.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

</th>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:emergency" title="Key:emergency"> emergency</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:emergency%3Dambulance_station" title="Tag:emergency=ambulance station"> ambulance_station</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An ambulance station is a structure or other area set aside for storage of ambulance vehicles, medical equipment, personal protective equipment, and other medical supplies.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Amb_station.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Amb station.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/c/ce/Amb_station.JPG/100px-Amb_station.JPG" width="100" height="81" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/ce/Amb_station.JPG/150px-Amb_station.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/ce/Amb_station.JPG/200px-Amb_station.JPG 2x" /></a></div></div>

<td> An Automated External Defibrillator (AED) is a first-aid device that automates the process of diagnosing life-threatening cardiac arrhythmia and performing defibrillation. Previously tagged as <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:emergency" title="Key:emergency">emergency</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:emergency%3Daed" title="Tag:emergency=aed" class="mw-redirect">aed</a></tt> or <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Key:medical&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Key:medical (page does not exist)">medical</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:medical%3Daed" title="Tag:medical=aed" class="mw-redirect">aed</a></tt>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Jt osm defi ibis.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/b/bf/Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg/100px-Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/b/bf/Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg/150px-Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/b/bf/Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg/200px-Jt_osm_defi_ibis.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

</td>
<td> A fire extinguisher is an active fire protection device used to extinguish or control small fires, often in emergency situations.
</td>

</td>
<td> A flapper is a wildland firefighting tool also called a swatter or a beater. It is designed for extinguishing minor fires in rural areas such as heaths.
</td>

</td>
<td> A fire hose is a high-pressure hose used to carry water or other fire retardant (such as foam) to a fire to extinguish it.
</td>
<td>
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> A fire hydrant is an active fire protection measure, and a source of water provided in most urban, suburban and rural areas with municipal water service or other water source to enable firefighters to tap into the municipal water supply to assist in extinguishing a fire.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Downtown Charlottesville fire hydrant.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/5a/Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg/100px-Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg" width="100" height="133" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/5a/Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg/150px-Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/5a/Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg/200px-Downtown_Charlottesville_fire_hydrant.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Geological">Geological</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe the geological makeup of an area.  See <a href="/wiki/Geological" title="Geological">Geological</a> for further information.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" width="100%">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th> Comment
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:geological" title="Key:geological"> geological</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:geological%3Doutcrop" title="Tag:geological=outcrop"> outcrop</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An outcrop site is a place where the bedrock or superficial deposits have become locally exposed and are directly accessible to analysis.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Buntsandstein.png" class="image"><img alt="Buntsandstein.png" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1f/Buntsandstein.png/80px-Buntsandstein.png" width="80" height="107" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/1f/Buntsandstein.png/120px-Buntsandstein.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/1f/Buntsandstein.png/160px-Buntsandstein.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:geological" title="Key:geological"> geological</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/w/index.php?title=Tag:geological%3Dmoraine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Tag:geological=moraine (page does not exist)"> moraine</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td>  A moraine is any ice formed accumulation of unconsolidated glacial debris (soil and rock) which can occur in currently glaciated and formerly glaciated regions, such as those areas acted upon by glacial ice.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:GornerGlacier.jpg" class="image"><img alt="GornerGlacier.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1b/GornerGlacier.jpg/80px-GornerGlacier.jpg" width="80" height="53" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/1b/GornerGlacier.jpg/120px-GornerGlacier.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/1b/GornerGlacier.jpg/160px-GornerGlacier.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:geological" title="Key:geological"> geological</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:geological%3Dpalaeontological_site" title="Tag:geological=palaeontological site"> palaeontological_site</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> A palaeontological site is a place (or group of physical sites) in which remains of ancient living forms is preserved. Area under the study of the forms of life existing in prehistoric times, as represented by the fossils of plants, animals, and other organisms investigated using the discipline of palaeontology.
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Palaeontological_site.svg" class="image"><img alt="Palaeontological site.svg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/4d/Palaeontological_site.svg/60px-Palaeontological_site.svg.png" width="60" height="65" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/4d/Palaeontological_site.svg/90px-Palaeontological_site.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/4d/Palaeontological_site.svg/120px-Palaeontological_site.svg.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Giacimento paleontologico villaggio del pescatore duino.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1d/Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg/80px-Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/1d/Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg/120px-Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/1d/Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg/160px-Giacimento_paleontologico_villaggio_del_pescatore_duino.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>

<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This table is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:geological" title="Template:Map Features:geological">Editable here</a>.</span>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Highway">Highway</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe roads and footpaths. See <a href="/wiki/Highways" title="Highways">Highways</a> for further guidance and <a href="/wiki/Restrictions" title="Restrictions">Restrictions</a> for details of access limitations by vehicle type/ time/ day/ load/ purpose etc.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th class="unsortable"> Comment
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Photo

<th colspan="7">
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Roads">Roads</span></h4>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="7">
<p>The principal tags for the road network, from most to least important
</p>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dmotorway" title="Tag:highway=motorway"> motorway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A restricted access major divided highway, normally with 2 or more running lanes plus emergency hard shoulder. Equivalent to the Freeway, Autobahn, etc..
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway motorway neutral.png" src="/w/images/thumb/6/6a/Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png/100px-Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png" width="100" height="68" srcset="/w/images/thumb/6/6a/Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png/150px-Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/6a/Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png/200px-Rendering-highway_motorway_neutral.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Motorway-photo.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Motorway-photo.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/6/60/Motorway-photo.jpg/100px-Motorway-photo.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/6/60/Motorway-photo.jpg/150px-Motorway-photo.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/60/Motorway-photo.jpg/200px-Motorway-photo.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dtrunk" title="Tag:highway=trunk"> trunk</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The most important roads in a country's system that aren't motorways. (Need not necessarily be a divided highway.)
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_trunk_neutral.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway trunk neutral.png" src="/w/images/thumb/7/71/Rendering-highway_trunk_neutral.png/100px-Rendering-highway_trunk_neutral.png" width="100" height="57" srcset="/w/images/7/71/Rendering-highway_trunk_neutral.png 1.5x, /w/images/7/71/Rendering-highway_trunk_neutral.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Dscf0444_600.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Dscf0444 600.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d4/Dscf0444_600.jpg/100px-Dscf0444_600.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d4/Dscf0444_600.jpg/150px-Dscf0444_600.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d4/Dscf0444_600.jpg/200px-Dscf0444_600.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dprimary" title="Tag:highway=primary"> primary</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The next most important roads in a country's system. (Often link larger towns.)
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_primary_neutral.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway primary neutral.png" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d9/Rendering-highway_primary_neutral.png/100px-Rendering-highway_primary_neutral.png" width="100" height="57" srcset="/w/images/d/d9/Rendering-highway_primary_neutral.png 1.5x, /w/images/d/d9/Rendering-highway_primary_neutral.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Primary-photo.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Primary-photo.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c3/Primary-photo.jpg/100px-Primary-photo.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c3/Primary-photo.jpg/150px-Primary-photo.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c3/Primary-photo.jpg/200px-Primary-photo.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dsecondary" title="Tag:highway=secondary"> secondary</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The next most important roads in a country's system. (Often link smaller towns and villages.)
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_secondary_neutral.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway secondary neutral.png" src="/w/images/4/42/Rendering-highway_secondary_neutral.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Meyenburg-L134.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Meyenburg-L134.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/17/Meyenburg-L134.jpg/100px-Meyenburg-L134.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/17/Meyenburg-L134.jpg/150px-Meyenburg-L134.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/17/Meyenburg-L134.jpg/200px-Meyenburg-L134.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dtertiary" title="Tag:highway=tertiary"> tertiary</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The next most important roads in a country's system.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_tertiary_neutral.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway tertiary neutral.png" src="/w/images/4/4d/Rendering-highway_tertiary_neutral.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg" class="image"><img alt="OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer Str.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg/100px-OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg/150px-OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg/200px-OHZ-K28-Bergedorfer_Str.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dunclassified" title="Tag:highway=unclassified"> unclassified</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The least most important through roads in a country's system - i.e. minor roads of a lower classification than tertiary, but which serve a purpose other than access to properties. (The word 'unclassified' is a historical artefact of the UK road system and does <b>not</b> mean that the classification is unknown; you can use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Droad" title="Tag:highway=road">road</a></tt> for that.)
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_unclassified.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway unclassified.png" src="/w/images/3/34/Rendering-highway_unclassified.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td>   <a href="/wiki/File:Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Highway unclassified-photo.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/8/80/Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg/100px-Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/8/80/Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg/150px-Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/8/80/Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg/200px-Highway_unclassified-photo.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dresidential" title="Tag:highway=residential"> residential</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Roads which are primarily lined with and serve as an access to housing.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_residential.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway residential.png" src="/w/images/5/57/Rendering-highway_residential.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Residential.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Residential.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/3/30/Residential.jpg/100px-Residential.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/30/Residential.jpg/150px-Residential.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/30/Residential.jpg/200px-Residential.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dservice" title="Tag:highway=service"> service</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For access roads to, or within an industrial estate, camp site, business park, car park etc. Can be used in conjunction with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:service" title="Key:service">service</a>=*</tt> to indicate the type of usage and with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:access" title="Key:access">access</a>=*</tt> to indicate who can use it and in what circumstances.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_service.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway service.png" src="/w/images/7/7f/Rendering-highway_service.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Alley.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Alley.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3a/Alley.jpg/100px-Alley.jpg" width="100" height="97" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3a/Alley.jpg/150px-Alley.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3a/Alley.jpg/200px-Alley.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<p>Link roads
</p>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dmotorway_link" title="Tag:highway=motorway link"> motorway_link</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The link roads (sliproads/ramps) leading to/from a motorway from/to a motorway or lower class highway. Normally with the same motorway restrictions.
</td>

<p>Special road types
</p>
</th></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dliving_street" title="Tag:highway=living street"> living_street</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/living_street" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:living street">living streets</a>, which are residential streets where pedestrians have legal priority over cars, speeds are kept very low and where children are allowed to play on the street.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Living_street_osm.png" class="image"><img alt="Living street osm.png" src="/w/images/thumb/1/10/Living_street_osm.png/100px-Living_street_osm.png" width="100" height="65" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/10/Living_street_osm.png/150px-Living_street_osm.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/10/Living_street_osm.png/200px-Living_street_osm.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Spielstrasse.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Spielstrasse.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/6/6a/Spielstrasse.jpg/100px-Spielstrasse.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/6/6a/Spielstrasse.jpg/150px-Spielstrasse.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/6a/Spielstrasse.jpg/200px-Spielstrasse.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dpedestrian" title="Tag:highway=pedestrian"> pedestrian</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For roads used mainly/exclusively for pedestrians in shopping and some residential areas which may allow access by motorised vehicles only for very limited periods of the day. To create a 'square' or 'plaza' create a closed way and tag as pedestrian and also with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:area" title="Key:area">area</a>=yes</tt>.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png" class="image"><img alt="Pedestrian with area osm.png" src="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png/100px-Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png" width="100" height="88" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png/150px-Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/07/Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png/200px-Pedestrian_with_area_osm.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Calle_arenal.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Calle arenal.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d8/Calle_arenal.jpg/100px-Calle_arenal.jpg" width="100" height="77" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d8/Calle_arenal.jpg/150px-Calle_arenal.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d8/Calle_arenal.jpg/200px-Calle_arenal.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dtrack" title="Tag:highway=track"> track</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Roads for agricultural or forestry uses etc, often rough with unpaved/unsealed surfaces. <b>In countries where most roads are unpaved, you should still use the main trunk/primary/secondary/tertiary/unclassified values</b>, making sure to also tag the surface type. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:surface" title="Key:surface">surface</a>=*</tt> or <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:tracktype" title="Key:tracktype">tracktype</a>=*</tt> for tagging to describe the surface.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_track.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway track.png" src="/w/images/8/86/Rendering-highway_track.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Frühlingslandschft Aaretal Schweiz.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/f/f6/Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg/100px-Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/f6/Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg/150px-Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/f/f6/Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg/200px-Fr%C3%BChlingslandschft_Aaretal_Schweiz.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dbus_guideway" title="Tag:highway=bus guideway"> bus_guideway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A busway where the vehicle guided by the way (though not a railway) and is not suitable for other traffic. Please note: this is not a normal bus lane, use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:access" title="Key:access">access</a>=no</tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:psv" title="Key:psv">psv</a>=yes</tt> instead!
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Bus_track.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Bus track.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/7/7a/Bus_track.jpg/100px-Bus_track.jpg" width="100" height="63" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/7a/Bus_track.jpg/150px-Bus_track.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/7a/Bus_track.jpg/200px-Bus_track.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Draceway" title="Tag:highway=raceway"> raceway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A course or track for (motor) racing
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/thumb/9/97/Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png/100px-Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png" width="100" height="95" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/97/Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png/150px-Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/97/Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png/200px-Rendering-highway-raceway-mapnik.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Raceway.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Raceway.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/9/9e/Raceway.jpg/100px-Raceway.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/9e/Raceway.jpg/150px-Raceway.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/9e/Raceway.jpg/200px-Raceway.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Droad" title="Tag:highway=road"> road</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A road where the mapper is unable to ascertain the classification from the information available. This is intended as a temporary tag to mark a road until it has been properly surveyed. Once it has been surveyed, the classification should be updated to the appropriate value.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Road.png" class="image"><img alt="Road.png" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d7/Road.png/100px-Road.png" width="100" height="86" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d7/Road.png/150px-Road.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d7/Road.png/200px-Road.png 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="7">
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Paths">Paths</span></h4>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dfootway" title="Tag:highway=footway"> footway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For designated footpaths; i.e., mainly/exclusively for pedestrians. This includes walking tracks and gravel paths. If bicycles are allowed as well, you can indicate this by adding a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:bicycle" title="Key:bicycle">bicycle</a>=yes</tt> tag.  Should not be used for paths where the primary or intended usage is unknown. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dpedestrian" title="Tag:highway=pedestrian">pedestrian</a></tt> for pedestrianised roads in shopping or residential areas and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dtrack" title="Tag:highway=track">track</a></tt> if it is usable by agricultural or similar vehicles.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_footway.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway footway.png" src="/w/images/b/b7/Rendering-highway_footway.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Dscf0487_600.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Dscf0487 600.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/6/64/Dscf0487_600.jpg/100px-Dscf0487_600.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/6/64/Dscf0487_600.jpg/150px-Dscf0487_600.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/64/Dscf0487_600.jpg/200px-Dscf0487_600.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dbridleway" title="Tag:highway=bridleway"> bridleway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For horses. Equivalent to <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dpath" title="Tag:highway=path">path</a></tt> + <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:horse" title="Key:horse">horse</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:horse%3Ddesignated" title="Tag:horse=designated" class="mw-redirect">designated</a></tt>.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_bridleway.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway bridleway.png" src="/w/images/a/af/Rendering-highway_bridleway.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/f/fb/Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg/100px-Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/fb/Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg/150px-Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/f/fb/Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg/200px-Bridleway-reitweg-de.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dsteps" title="Tag:highway=steps"> steps</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For flights of steps (stairs) on footways. Use with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:step_count" title="Key:step count">step_count</a>=*</tt> to indicate the number of steps
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-highway_steps.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-highway steps.png" src="/w/images/4/44/Rendering-highway_steps.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Steps.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Steps.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/58/Steps.jpg/100px-Steps.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/58/Steps.jpg/150px-Steps.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/58/Steps.jpg/200px-Steps.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dpath" title="Tag:highway=path">path</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A non-specific or shared-use path. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dfootway" title="Tag:highway=footway">footway</a></tt> for paths mainly for walkers,  <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dcycleway" title="Tag:highway=cycleway">cycleway</a></tt> for one also usable by cyclists, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dbridleway" title="Tag:highway=bridleway">bridleway</a></tt> for ones available to horses as well as walkers and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dtrack" title="Tag:highway=track">track</a></tt> for ones which is passable by agriculture or similar vehicles.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Path_osm.png" class="image"><img alt="Path osm.png" src="/w/images/thumb/9/93/Path_osm.png/100px-Path_osm.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/93/Path_osm.png/150px-Path_osm.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/93/Path_osm.png/200px-Path_osm.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg" class="image"><img alt="GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/49/GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg/100px-GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/49/GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg/150px-GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/49/GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg/200px-GuideFootPathCycleYes.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<th colspan="7">
<p>When sidewalk (or pavement) is tagged on the main roadway (see <a href="/wiki/Sidewalks" title="Sidewalks">Sidewalks</a>)
</p>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:sidewalk" title="Key:sidewalk"> sidewalk</a>
</td>
<td> both / left / right / yes / no
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Specifies that the highway has sidewalks on both sides, on one side or no sidewalk at all
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Sidewalk and zebra-crossing.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/b/b9/Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg/100px-Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/b/b9/Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg/150px-Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/b/b9/Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg/200px-Sidewalk_and_zebra-crossing.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<th colspan="7">
<p>When cycleway is drawn as its own way (see <a href="/wiki/Bicycle" title="Bicycle">Bicycle</a>)
</p>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dcycleway" title="Tag:highway=cycleway"> cycleway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For designated cycleways. Add <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:foot" title="Key:foot">foot</a>=*</tt> only if <a href="/wiki/OSM_tags_for_routing/Access-Restrictions" title="OSM tags for routing/Access-Restrictions">default-access-restrictions</a> do not apply.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Cycleway_osm.png" class="image"><img alt="Cycleway osm.png" src="/w/images/2/28/Cycleway_osm.png" width="100" height="100" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg" class="image" title="Separated cycleway with traffic sign"><img alt="Separated cycleway with traffic sign" src="/w/images/thumb/4/46/Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg/100px-Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg" width="100" height="74" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/46/Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg/150px-Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/46/Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg/200px-Rotterdam_Fietspad_Westzeedijk.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="7">
<p>When cycleway or lane is tagged on the main roadway (see <a href="/wiki/Bicycle" title="Bicycle">Bicycle</a>)
</p>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:cycleway" title="Key:cycleway"> cycleway</a>
</td>
<td> lane
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A lane is a route that lies within the roadway
</td>
<td>
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:proposed" title="Key:proposed"> highway</a>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For planned roads, use with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:proposed" title="Key:proposed">proposed</a>=*</tt> and also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:proposed" title="Key:proposed">proposed</a>=*</tt> with a value of the proposed highway value.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:ford" title="Key:ford"> ford</a>

<td> yes
</td>

</td>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:ice_road%3Dyes" title="Tag:ice road=yes" class="mw-redirect">yes</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A highway is laid upon frozen water basin, definitely doesn't exist in summer.
</td>

</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:incline" title="Key:incline">incline</a>
</td>
<td> Number&#160;%/°
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Incline steepness as percents ("5%") or degrees ("20°"). Positive/negative values indicate movement upward/downwards in the direction of the way.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:junction" title="Key:junction"> junction</a>
</td>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Closed way"><img alt="Closed way" src="/w/images/thumb/3/38/Osm_element_closedway.svg/20px-Osm_element_closedway.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/38/Osm_element_closedway.svg/30px-Osm_element_closedway.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/38/Osm_element_closedway.svg/40px-Osm_element_closedway.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> This automatically implies <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:oneway" title="Key:oneway">oneway</a>=yes</tt>, the oneway direction is defined by the sequential ordering of nodes within the Way. This applies on a way, tagged with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=*</tt> already.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The motorroad tag is used to describe highways that have motorway-like access restrictions but that are not a motorway.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png" class="image"><img alt="120px-Zeichen 331.svg.png" src="/w/images/thumb/f/f2/120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png/60px-120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png" width="60" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/f2/120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png/90px-120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/f/f2/120px-Zeichen_331.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dbus_stop" title="Tag:highway=bus stop"> bus_stop</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A small bus stop. Can be mapped more rigorously using <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:public_transport" title="Key:public transport">public_transport</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:public_transport%3Dstop_position" title="Tag:public transport=stop position">stop_position</a></tt> for the position where the vehicle stops and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:public_transport" title="Key:public transport">public_transport</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:public_transport%3Dplatform" title="Tag:public transport=platform">platform</a></tt> for the place where passengers wait. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:public_transport" title="Key:public transport">public_transport</a>=*</tt> for more details.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dmini_roundabout" title="Tag:highway=mini roundabout"> mini_roundabout</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Similar to roundabouts, but at the center there is either a painted circle or a fully <a href="/wiki/Traversable" title="Traversable">traversable</a> island. In case of an untraversable center island, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:junction" title="Key:junction">junction</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:junction%3Droundabout" title="Tag:junction=roundabout">roundabout</a></tt> should be used.
<p>Rendered as anti-clockwise by default <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:direction" title="Key:direction">direction</a>=<a href="/w/index.php?title=Tag:direction%3Danticlockwise&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Tag:direction=anticlockwise (page does not exist)">anticlockwise</a></tt>. To render clockwise add the tag <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:direction" title="Key:direction">direction</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:direction%3Dclockwise" title="Tag:direction=clockwise" class="mw-redirect">clockwise</a></tt>.
</p>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png" class="image"><img alt="Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png" src="/w/images/thumb/0/02/Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png/100px-Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png" width="100" height="70" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/02/Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png/150px-Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/02/Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png/200px-Mapping-Features-Mini-Roundabout.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mini-roundabout.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Mini-roundabout.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/b/b0/Mini-roundabout.jpg/100px-Mini-roundabout.jpg" width="100" height="47" srcset="/w/images/thumb/b/b0/Mini-roundabout.jpg/150px-Mini-roundabout.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/b/b0/Mini-roundabout.jpg/200px-Mini-roundabout.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dturning_circle" title="Tag:highway=turning circle"> turning_circle</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A turning circle is a rounded, widened area usually, but not necessarily, at the end of a road to facilitate easier turning of a vehicle. Also known as a <i>cul de sac</i>.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png" class="image"><img alt="Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png" src="/w/images/thumb/8/8e/Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png/100px-Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png" width="100" height="80" srcset="/w/images/thumb/8/8e/Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png/150px-Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png 1.5x, /w/images/8/8e/Mapping-Features-Turning-Circle.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Turning_circle.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Turning circle.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3f/Turning_circle.jpg/100px-Turning_circle.jpg" width="100" height="65" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3f/Turning_circle.jpg/150px-Turning_circle.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3f/Turning_circle.jpg/200px-Turning_circle.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway"> highway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Proposed_features" title="Proposed features" class="mw-redirect"> User Defined</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>

</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Historic">Historic</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe various archeological sites, wrecks, ruins, castles and ancient buildings. See <a href="/wiki/Historic" title="Historic">Historic</a> for further details on usage.
</p>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:historic%3Druins" title="Tag:historic=ruins"> ruins</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Remains of structures that were once complete, but have fallen into partial or complete disrepair. If the type of original structure is known or apparent it can be described using <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:ruins" title="Key:ruins">ruins</a>=*</tt>, e.g. <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:ruins" title="Key:ruins">ruins</a>=castle</tt>.<br />
<p>Alternative tagging is <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:historic" title="Key:historic">historic</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:historic%3Dcastle" title="Tag:historic=castle">castle</a></tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:ruins" title="Key:ruins">ruins</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:ruins%3Dyes" title="Tag:ruins=yes" class="mw-redirect">yes</a></tt>.<br />
See the proposal and discussion at <a href="/wiki/Proposed_features/ruins" title="Proposed features/ruins">Proposed_features/ruins</a> for ruins of historic buildings. 
</p>
</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Landuse">Landuse</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe the purpose for which and area of land is being used. See <a href="/wiki/Landuse" title="Landuse">Landuse</a> for more information on the use of this tag.

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dbasin" title="Tag:landuse=basin"> basin</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An area of water that drains into a river.<br />Together with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:basin" title="Key:basin">basin</a>=*</tt> for stormwater/rainwater infiltration/detention/retention basins.<br /><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.omegawiki.org/DefinedMeaning:basin_(389120)">Other languages</a>.
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Landuse-basin.png" class="image"><img alt="Landuse-basin.png" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1f/Landuse-basin.png/80px-Landuse-basin.png" width="80" height="64" srcset="/w/images/1/1f/Landuse-basin.png 1.5x, /w/images/1/1f/Landuse-basin.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Wasserspeicher an Essens höchstem Punkt DSCF1228.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/b/bd/Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg/80px-Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/b/bd/Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg/120px-Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/b/bd/Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg/160px-Wasserspeicher_an_Essens_h%C3%B6chstem_Punkt_DSCF1228.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-brownfield">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dbrownfield" title="Tag:landuse=brownfield"> brownfield</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> Describes land scheduled for new development where old buildings have been demolished and cleared
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Landuse-brownfield.png" class="image"><img alt="Landuse-brownfield.png" src="/w/images/a/ad/Landuse-brownfield.png" width="80" height="68" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Former Brickworks ... - geograph.org.uk - 56268.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/2/2d/Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg/80px-Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/2/2d/Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg/120px-Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/2/2d/Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg/160px-Former_Brickworks_..._-_geograph.org.uk_-_56268.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-cemetery">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dcemetery" title="Tag:landuse=cemetery"> cemetery</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> Place for burials. You can add <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:religion" title="Key:religion">religion</a>=*</tt> (values listed in the <a href="/wiki/Tag:amenity%3Dplace_of_worship" title="Tag:amenity=place of worship">place of worship page</a>). Smaller places (e.g. with a church nearby) may use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:amenity" title="Key:amenity">amenity</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:amenity%3Dgrave_yard" title="Tag:amenity=grave yard">grave_yard</a></tt> instead.
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Landuse-cemetery.png" class="image"><img alt="Landuse-cemetery.png" src="/w/images/thumb/2/25/Landuse-cemetery.png/80px-Landuse-cemetery.png" width="80" height="80" srcset="/w/images/thumb/2/25/Landuse-cemetery.png/120px-Landuse-cemetery.png 1.5x, /w/images/2/25/Landuse-cemetery.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Cemetery-photo.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Cemetery-photo.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d4/Cemetery-photo.JPG/80px-Cemetery-photo.JPG" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d4/Cemetery-photo.JPG/120px-Cemetery-photo.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d4/Cemetery-photo.JPG/160px-Cemetery-photo.JPG 2x" /></a></div></div>

<tr id="landuse-farm">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dfarm" title="Tag:landuse=farm"> farm</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An area of farmland used for tillage and pasture (animals, crops, vegetables, flowers, fruit growing).
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png/80px-Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png/120px-Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/07/Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png/160px-Rendering-landuse-farm-mapnik.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Farm_landuse_(with_livestock).jpg" class="image"><img alt="Farm landuse (with livestock).jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/4e/Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg/80px-Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/4e/Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg/120px-Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/4e/Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg/160px-Farm_landuse_%28with_livestock%29.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-farmland">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dfarmland" title="Tag:landuse=farmland" class="mw-redirect"> farmland</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> Synonyme for <b>farm</b>, used in JOSM because <i>farm</i> was considered ambiguous. <i>Farmland</i> has been used more often as of 2013-02-21 (610 472 tags vs 453 935). See <a class="external text" href="http://josm.openstreetmap.de/ticket/1579">ticket #1579</a>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Rye_field.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Rye field.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/a/a1/Rye_field.jpg/80px-Rye_field.jpg" width="80" height="108" srcset="/w/images/thumb/a/a1/Rye_field.jpg/120px-Rye_field.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/a/a1/Rye_field.jpg/160px-Rye_field.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-farmyard">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dfarmyard" title="Tag:landuse=farmyard"> farmyard</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An area of land with farm buildings like farmhouse, dwellings, farmsteads, sheds, stables, barns, equipment sheds, feed bunkers, etc. plus the open space in between them and the shrubbery/trees around them.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Farmyard.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Farmyard.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c1/Farmyard.jpg/80px-Farmyard.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c1/Farmyard.jpg/120px-Farmyard.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c1/Farmyard.jpg/160px-Farmyard.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-forest">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dforest" title="Tag:landuse=forest"> forest</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> Managed forest or woodland plantation (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.omegawiki.org/DefinedMeaning:forest_(1533)">Other languages</a>).
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Landuse-forest.png" class="image"><img alt="Landuse-forest.png" src="/w/images/thumb/0/0c/Landuse-forest.png/80px-Landuse-forest.png" width="80" height="80" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/0c/Landuse-forest.png/120px-Landuse-forest.png 1.5x, /w/images/0/0c/Landuse-forest.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Forest.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Forest.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3a/Forest.jpg/80px-Forest.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3a/Forest.jpg/120px-Forest.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3a/Forest.jpg/160px-Forest.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-garages">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dgarages" title="Tag:landuse=garages"> garages</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> One level buildings with boxes commonly for cars, usually made of brick and metal. Usualy this area belong to garage cooperative with own name, chairman, budget, rules, security, etc.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Garages.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Garages.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/f/ff/Garages.jpg/80px-Garages.jpg" width="80" height="53" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/ff/Garages.jpg/120px-Garages.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/f/ff/Garages.jpg/160px-Garages.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-grass">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dgrass" title="Tag:landuse=grass"> grass</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> For areas covered with grass. Consider <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse">landuse</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dmeadow" title="Tag:landuse=meadow">meadow</a></tt> for meadow and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse">landuse</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dpasture" title="Tag:landuse=pasture" class="mw-redirect">pasture</a></tt> for pasture. Note that this is actually a <a href="/wiki/Landcover" title="Landcover">Landcover</a> tag, not a landuse tag and there is <a href="/wiki/Proposed_features/landcover" title="Proposed features/landcover">a proposal to deprecate it</a>.
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Mapnik_landuse_grass_.png" class="image"><img alt="Mapnik landuse grass .png" src="/w/images/thumb/b/b8/Mapnik_landuse_grass_.png/80px-Mapnik_landuse_grass_.png" width="80" height="80" srcset="/w/images/b/b8/Mapnik_landuse_grass_.png 1.5x, /w/images/b/b8/Mapnik_landuse_grass_.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Grasss.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Grasss.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/19/Grasss.jpg/80px-Grasss.jpg" width="80" height="52" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/19/Grasss.jpg/120px-Grasss.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/19/Grasss.jpg/160px-Grasss.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr id="landuse-greenfield">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dgreenfield" title="Tag:landuse=greenfield"> greenfield</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> Describes land scheduled for new development where there have been no buildings before. A greenfield is scheduled to turn into a construction site

<tr id="landuse-meadow">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dmeadow" title="Tag:landuse=meadow"> meadow</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> An area of land primarily vegetated by grass and other non-woody plants, usually mowed for making hay (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.omegawiki.org/DefinedMeaning:meadow_(2295)">Other Languages</a>).
</td>

<tr id="landuse-reservoir">
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse"> landuse</a>
</td>

</td>
<td> Stores water, may be covered or uncovered; for a covered reservoir see also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:man_made" title="Key:man made">man_made</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:man_made%3Dreservoir_covered" title="Tag:man made=reservoir covered">reservoir_covered</a></tt> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.omegawiki.org/DefinedMeaning:reservoir_(3196)">Other languages</a>). See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:water" title="Key:water">water</a>=reservoir</tt> for alternative tagging.
</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Leisure">Leisure</span></h3>
<p>Used to tag leisure and sports facilities. See <a href="/wiki/Leisure" title="Leisure">Leisure</a> for a general introduction.

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Man_Made">Man Made</span></h3>
<p>A tag for identifying man made (artificial) structures added to the landscape. See <a href="/wiki/Man-made" title="Man-made">Man-made</a> for an introduction.

</td>
<td> A raised bank to carry a road, railway, or canal across a low-lying or wet area.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>

</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Silo.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Silo.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/a/aa/Silo.jpg/100px-Silo.jpg" width="100" height="80" srcset="/w/images/thumb/a/aa/Silo.jpg/150px-Silo.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/a/aa/Silo.jpg/200px-Silo.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:man_made" title="Key:man made"> man_made</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:man_made%3Dsnow_fence" title="Tag:man made=snow fence"> snow_fence</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/snow_fence" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:snow fence">snow fence</a> is a solid fence-like structure built across steep slopes to reduce risk and severity of (snow) avalanches. Usually made of steel, sloping outwards, and trussed underneath. Sometimes refered to as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/snow_shed" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:snow shed">snow shed</a>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Verbauung Tanngrindel.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/9/9d/Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG/100px-Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/9d/Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG/150px-Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/9d/Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG/200px-Verbauung_Tanngrindel.JPG 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:man_made%3Dsnow_fence" title="Tag:man made=snow fence"> snow_net</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/snow_net" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:snow net">snow net</a> netting fence built across steep slopes to reduce risk and severity of (snow) avalanches. They consist of a net made of steel cables, held up by posts. Sometimes refered to as an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avalanche_net" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Avalanche net">Avalanche net</a>.
</td>
<td>
</td>

</td>
<td> Windmill, mostly ancient and out of order, see <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dgenerator" title="Tag:power=generator">generator</a></tt> in combination with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:generator:source" title="Key:generator:source">generator:source</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:generator:source%3Dwind" title="Tag:generator:source=wind">wind</a></tt> for modern wind turbines

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Military">Military</span></h3>
<p>Used for facilities and land used by the military, including the Navy, Army, Airforce and Marines. See <a href="/wiki/Military" title="Military">Military</a> for an introduction.
</p>

</td>
<td> Where soldiers have practice with their weapons (firing, bombing, artillery, ...).

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Natural">Natural</span></h3>
<p>Used to describes natural physical land features, including ones that have been modified by humans. See <a href="/wiki/Natural" title="Natural">Natural</a> for an introduction.
</p>
<table class="wikitable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>

<td> An <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ar%C3%AAte" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Arête">arête</a>, a thin, almost knife-like, ridge of rock which is typically formed when two glaciers erode parallel U-shaped valleys.

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Office">Office</span></h3>
<p>An office is a place of business where administrative or professional work is carried out.
</p>

</td>

<p>Used mainly to give details about settlements.

</td>
