</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dmunicipality" title="Tag:place=municipality" class="mw-redirect"> municipality</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:boundary" title="Key:boundary">boundary</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:boundary%3Dadministrative" title="Tag:boundary=administrative">administrative</a></tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:admin_level" title="Key:admin level" class="mw-redirect">admin_level</a>=*</tt> varies; depending on the country a collection of arbitrary hamlets, villages and towns may form an administrative unit; sometimes members of a unit reform or join with another municipality as a result of political process.  Within a municipality individual settlements are a lot less connected than those within a city, where they have grown connected over time.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> Populated settlements, urban
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dcity" title="Tag:place=city"> city</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The largest urban settlements in the territory, normally including the national, state and provincial capitals. These are defined by charter or other governmental designation in some territories and are a matter of judgement in others. Should normally have a population of at least 100,000 people and be larger than nearby towns. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dsuburb" title="Tag:place=suburb">suburb</a></tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dneighbourhood" title="Tag:place=neighbourhood">neighbourhood</a></tt> on how to tag divisions within a city. The outskirts of urban settlements may or may not match the administratively declared boundary of the city.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/w/index.php?title=Tag:place%3Dborough&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Tag:place=borough (page does not exist)"> borough</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:boundary" title="Key:boundary">boundary</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:boundary%3Dadministrative" title="Tag:boundary=administrative">administrative</a></tt>, depending on the country suburbs in larger cities are often grouped into administrative units called <i>borough</i>s or <i>city district</i>s; using the value <i>borough</i> avoids name confusion in countries that declare districts within their states or counties.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dsuburb" title="Tag:place=suburb"> suburb</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A distinct section of an urban settlement (city, town, etc.) with its own name and identity.  e.g.
<ul>
<li> annexed towns or villages which were formerly independent,
</li>
<li> independent (or dependent) municipalities within a city or next to a much bigger town 
</li>
<li> historical districts of settlements
</li>
<li> industrial districts or recreation areas within a settlements with specific names.
</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dquarter" title="Tag:place=quarter" class="mw-redirect"> quarter</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A named part of a bigger settlement where this part is smaller then a suburb and bigger then a neighbourhood. This does not have to be an administrative entity.<br />The term <i>quarter</i> is sometimes used synonymously for <i>neighbourhood</i>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dneighbourhood" title="Tag:place=neighbourhood"> neighbourhood</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A named part of a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dvillage" title="Tag:place=village">village</a></tt>, a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dtown" title="Tag:place=town">town</a></tt> or a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dcity" title="Tag:place=city">city</a></tt>. Smaller than <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dsuburb" title="Tag:place=suburb">suburb</a></tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dquarter" title="Tag:place=quarter" class="mw-redirect">quarter</a></tt>.<br />The term <i>quarter</i> is sometimes used synonymously for <i>neighbourhood</i>, but may also stand for <i>borough</i> or <i>suburb</i> and hence is often avoided in OSM. See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Quarter_(urban_subdivision)" title="wikipedia:en:Quarter (urban subdivision)"><img alt="Wikipedia" src="/w/images/2/24/Wikipedia-16px.png" width="16" height="16" /></a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Quarter_(urban_subdivision)" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:en:Quarter (urban subdivision)">Quarter_(urban_subdivision)</a>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> Populated settlements, urban and rural
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dtown" title="Tag:place=town"> town</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A second tier urban settlement of local importance, often with a population of 10,000 people and good range of local facilities including schools, medical facilities etc and traditionally a market. In areas of low population, towns may have significantly lower populations. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dneighbourhood" title="Tag:place=neighbourhood">neighbourhood</a></tt> and possibly also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dsuburb" title="Tag:place=suburb">suburb</a></tt> on how to tag divisions within a town.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dvillage" title="Tag:place=village"> village</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A smaller distinct settlement, smaller than a town with few facilities available with people traveling to nearby towns to access these. Populations of villages vary widely in different territories but will nearly always be less than 10,000 people, often a lot less. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dneighbourhood" title="Tag:place=neighbourhood">neighbourhood</a></tt> on how to tag divisions within a larger village.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dhamlet" title="Tag:place=hamlet"> hamlet</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A smaller rural community typically with less than 100-200 inhabitants, few infrastructure.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Disolated_dwelling" title="Tag:place=isolated dwelling"> isolated_dwelling</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For a named settlement consisting of some two to three households in a secluded rural setting.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dfarm" title="Tag:place=farm"> farm</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A farm that has its own name. If the farm is not a part of bigger settlement use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Disolated_dwelling" title="Tag:place=isolated dwelling">isolated_dwelling</a></tt>. See also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse">landuse</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:landuse%3Dfarmyard" title="Tag:landuse=farmyard">farmyard</a></tt>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dallotments" title="Tag:place=allotments"> allotments</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td>  Dacha or cottage settlement, which is located outside  other inhabited locality. This value is used mainly in Russia and other countries of the former Soviet Union, where a lot of such unofficial settlements exist
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>

</th></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dcontinent" title="Tag:place=continent"> continent</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> One of the seven continents: Africa, Antarctica, Asia, Australia, Europe, North America, South America
</td>

</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Darchipelago" title="Tag:place=archipelago"> archipelago</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Relation" title="Relation"><img alt="Relation" src="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/20px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/30px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/40px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Identifies the relation of an archipelago, which contains several islands and islets.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Disland" title="Tag:place=island"> island</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Identifies the coastline of an island (&gt; 1 km<sup>2</sup>), also consider <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dislet" title="Tag:place=islet">islet</a></tt> for very small islands
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place"> place</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dislet" title="Tag:place=islet"> islet</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Identifies an islet (&lt; 1 km<sup>2</sup>).
</td>

<th colspan="6"> Additional attributes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:population" title="Key:population"> population</a>
</td>
<td>  Number
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Number of inhabitants of the place. Among other things, it might be used in selecting which name to render at a given zoom level at what font size.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:name" title="Key:name">  name</a>
</td>
<td>  Text
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> To define the name of a place.

</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:reference_point" title="Key:reference point"> reference_point</a>
</td>
<td>  yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Named landmarks used to identify locations (common in some countries).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:is_in" title="Key:is in"> is_in</a>
</td>
<td>  Text
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <i>Optional</i>. Rudimentary way to describe boundary hierarchies, e.g. <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:place" title="Key:place">place</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:place%3Dsuburb" title="Tag:place=suburb">suburb</a></tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:name" title="Key:name">name</a>=Eccleshall</tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:is_in" title="Key:is in">is_in</a>=Sheffield,South Yorkshire,England,UK</tt>. <i>If</i> boundary polygons exist, it's usually not needed.  Unless categorization is wrongly done by e.g. <a href="/wiki/Nominatim/FAQ#.23How_do_I_fix_the_address.3F" title="Nominatim/FAQ">Nominatim</a>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr></table>
<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This section is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:place" title="Template:Map Features:place">Editable here</a>.</span>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Power">Power</span></h3>
<p>Used to map electrical power generation and distributions systems. See <a href="/wiki/Power" title="Power">Power</a> for further information.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th class="unsortable"> Comment
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dcable" title="Tag:power=cable"> cable</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A way following the path of <b>underground cables</b>, such as the local 0.4 kV network between transformer stations, distribution boxes and cable connection points, or <b>sea cables</b>. Not to be confused with non-power supply cables such as cables for telecommunication. May be combined with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:location" title="Key:location">location</a>=underground/underwater/overground</tt>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Power to the People - geograph.org.uk - 560240.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/8/83/Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg/100px-Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/8/83/Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg/150px-Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/8/83/Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg/200px-Power_to_the_People_-_geograph.org.uk_-_560240.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dcable_distribution_cabinet" title="Tag:power=cable distribution cabinet"> cable_distribution_cabinet</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> In these cabinets, the 400-V circuits to the house connections, connection and transfer points of the regional utilities are branched. Other uses include distributions of the municipal street lighting.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Kvs2.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Kvs2.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/4d/Kvs2.jpg/100px-Kvs2.jpg" width="100" height="123" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/4d/Kvs2.jpg/150px-Kvs2.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/4d/Kvs2.jpg/200px-Kvs2.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dconverter" title="Tag:power=converter" class="mw-redirect"> converter</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> An <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HVDC_converter" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:HVDC converter">HVDC converter</a> converts electric power from high voltage alternating current (AC) to high-voltage direct current (HVDC), or vice-versa.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Pole 2 Thyristor Valve.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/04/Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg/100px-Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/04/Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg/150px-Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/04/Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg/200px-Pole_2_Thyristor_Valve.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dgenerator" title="Tag:power=generator"> generator</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Relation" title="Relation"><img alt="Relation" src="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/20px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/30px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/40px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A device used to convert power from one form to another. Use in combination with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:generator:source" title="Key:generator:source">generator:source</a>=*</tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:generator:method" title="Key:generator:method">generator:method</a>=*</tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:generator:output" title="Key:generator:output">generator:output</a>=*</tt>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Eoliennes Gaspesie.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d7/Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg/100px-Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d7/Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg/150px-Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d7/Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg/200px-Eoliennes_Gaspesie.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dline" title="Tag:power=line"> line</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A way following the path of (overground) power cables. For minor power lines with poles and not towers, you may want to use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dminor_line" title="Tag:power=minor line">minor_line</a></tt>.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Power-tower_mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Power-tower mapnik.png" src="/w/images/8/87/Power-tower_mapnik.png" width="100" height="86" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Electric_transmission_lines.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Electric transmission lines.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/6/66/Electric_transmission_lines.jpg/100px-Electric_transmission_lines.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/6/66/Electric_transmission_lines.jpg/150px-Electric_transmission_lines.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/66/Electric_transmission_lines.jpg/200px-Electric_transmission_lines.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dminor_line" title="Tag:power=minor line"> minor_line</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A way following the path of (overground) minor power cables, supported by poles and not towers/pylons. (This isn't quite so simple, as sometimes larger towers are replaced by smaller poles made with a stronger material; a better distinction might be based on voltage.)
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Minor_line_mapnik.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Minor line mapnik.jpg" src="/w/images/e/e5/Minor_line_mapnik.jpg" width="100" height="96" /></a>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Pole3.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Pole3.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/9/99/Pole3.jpg/70px-Pole3.jpg" width="70" height="112" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/99/Pole3.jpg/105px-Pole3.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/99/Pole3.jpg/140px-Pole3.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dplant" title="Tag:power=plant"> plant</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Relation" title="Relation"><img alt="Relation" src="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/20px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/30px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/48/Osm_element_relation.svg/40px-Osm_element_relation.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A place/industrial facility where power is generated. Use in combination with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dgenerator" title="Tag:power=generator">generator</a></tt>.
</td>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Huntly_Power_Station.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Huntly Power Station.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1d/Huntly_Power_Station.JPG/100px-Huntly_Power_Station.JPG" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/1d/Huntly_Power_Station.JPG/150px-Huntly_Power_Station.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/1d/Huntly_Power_Station.JPG/200px-Huntly_Power_Station.JPG 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dpole" title="Tag:power=pole"> pole</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For single (often wooden or concrete) poles carrying medium/low voltage electricity cables.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Minor_line_mapnik.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Minor line mapnik.jpg" src="/w/images/e/e5/Minor_line_mapnik.jpg" width="100" height="96" /></a>
</td>

</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dsubstation" title="Tag:power=substation"> substation</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A tag for electricity substations. These provide voltage step-up/step-down, switching, conditioning, etc. Substations may be large facilities (up to several acres) for very high voltage transmission lines or just small buildings or kiosks near the street for low voltage distribution lines.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/thumb/5/54/380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png/100px-380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/54/380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png/150px-380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/54/380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png/200px-380kv-bleiswijk-mapnik.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Substation.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Substation.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/5e/Substation.jpg/100px-Substation.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/5e/Substation.jpg/150px-Substation.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/5e/Substation.jpg/200px-Substation.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dswitch" title="Tag:power=switch" class="mw-redirect"> switch</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A tag for electricity switches which are devices which allow operators to power up &amp; down lines and transformer in substations or outside.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg" class="image"><img alt="French overhead power switch pole.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/08/French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg/100px-French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg" width="100" height="86" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/08/French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg/150px-French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/08/French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg/200px-French_overhead_power_switch_pole.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dtower" title="Tag:power=tower"> tower</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For towers or pylons carrying high voltage electricity cables. Normally constructed from steel latticework but tubular or solid pylons are also commonly used. Should not be used for medium or low voltage electricity conductors carried on single wooden poles which might be tagged <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dpole" title="Tag:power=pole">pole</a></tt>. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dtower" title="Tag:power=tower">tower</a></tt> for detailed tagging of tower types.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Power-tower_mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Power-tower mapnik.png" src="/w/images/8/87/Power-tower_mapnik.png" width="100" height="86" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Benkid77 Puddington-Shotwick footpath 24 110809.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/7/72/Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG/100px-Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/72/Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG/150px-Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/72/Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG/200px-Benkid77_Puddington-Shotwick_footpath_24_110809.JPG 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power"> power</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dtransformer" title="Tag:power=transformer"> transformer</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A static device for transferring electric energy by inductive coupling between its windings. Large power transformers are typically located inside substations
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Trafostation Alter Hellweg IMGP4722.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/a/a3/Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg/100px-Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/a/a3/Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg/150px-Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/a/a3/Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg/200px-Trafostation_Alter_Hellweg_IMGP4722.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:cables" title="Key:cables"> cables</a>
</td>
<td> 2, 3, 4, 6, 9, 12, ...
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Number of power-carrying cables represented by this way. The power line on the photo (click on it to see more details) has 6 double cables (the cable on top does not carry power) and thus may be tagged as <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:cables" title="Key:cables">cables</a>=6</tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:wires" title="Key:wires">wires</a>=double</tt>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Power-tower.JPG" class="image"><img alt="Power-tower.JPG" src="/w/images/thumb/0/01/Power-tower.JPG/100px-Power-tower.JPG" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/01/Power-tower.JPG/150px-Power-tower.JPG 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/01/Power-tower.JPG/200px-Power-tower.JPG 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:circuits" title="Key:circuits"> circuits</a>
</td>
<td> 1, 2, 3, ...
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Number of electrical circuits represented by this way. The tag may be used when the number of physical cables is unknown (often the case for underground cable connections) or when the number of circuits is different from <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:cables" title="Key:cables">cables</a>=*</tt> divided by 3. The photo shows a power line that connects to a cable connection having two circuits and thus may be tagged as <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:circuits" title="Key:circuits">circuits</a>=2</tt>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Onder- en bovengronds.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e2/Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg/100px-Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg" width="100" height="78" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e2/Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg/150px-Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e2/Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg/200px-Onder-_en_bovengronds.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:tunnel" title="Key:tunnel">tunnel</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Notes that a line or cable is contained in a self-supporting tunnel that may also be used for other purposes such as road traffic or be provided for maintenance purposes. Cables buried underground should not use this tag but be tagged as <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:power" title="Key:power">power</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:power%3Dcable" title="Tag:power=cable">cable</a></tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:location" title="Key:location">location</a>=underground/underwater/..</tt>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:voltage" title="Key:voltage"> voltage</a>
</td>
<td> ...,<br />110000,<br />220000,<br />380000,<br />...
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Voltage of the power line.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Tower_reference_sign.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Tower reference sign.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/5f/Tower_reference_sign.jpg/100px-Tower_reference_sign.jpg" width="100" height="72" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/5f/Tower_reference_sign.jpg/150px-Tower_reference_sign.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/5f/Tower_reference_sign.jpg/200px-Tower_reference_sign.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:wires" title="Key:wires"> wires</a>
</td>
<td> single, double, triple, quad
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Number of wires per power cable. "single" (1), "double" (2), "triple" (3) or "quad" (4). The photo shows an example of "double".
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Twin-bundle.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Twin-bundle.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/42/Twin-bundle.jpg/100px-Twin-bundle.jpg" width="100" height="89" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/42/Twin-bundle.jpg/150px-Twin-bundle.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/42/Twin-bundle.jpg/200px-Twin-bundle.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Railway">Railway</span></h3>
<p>Includes all kind of railway from heavy used mainline railway down to an abandoned line. See <a href="/wiki/Railways" title="Railways">Railways</a> for an introduction to mapping railways.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th class="unsortable"> Comment
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> Track
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dabandoned" title="Tag:railway=abandoned"> abandoned</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The course of a former railway which has been abandoned and the track and infrastucture removed. The course may be still recognized through embankments, cuttings, bridges, tunnel and rolling or straight ways.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge,_High_Wycombe,_Buckinghamshire.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Abbey Barn Lane Bridge, High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/8/83/Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg/100px-Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/8/83/Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg/150px-Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/8/83/Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg/200px-Abbey_Barn_Lane_Bridge%2C_High_Wycombe%2C_Buckinghamshire.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dconstruction" title="Tag:railway=construction" class="mw-redirect"> construction</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A railway under construction. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:construction" title="Key:construction">construction</a>=*</tt> and the <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:construction" title="Key:construction">construction</a>=yes</tt> proposal <a href="/wiki/Proposed_features/Construction" title="Proposed features/Construction">Proposed_features/Construction</a>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Verlegen FF Rheda.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/02/Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg/80px-Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg" width="80" height="53" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/02/Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg/120px-Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/02/Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg/160px-Verlegen_FF_Rheda.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Ddisused" title="Tag:railway=disused"> disused</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A section of railway which is no longer used but where the track and infrastructure remains in place. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:disused" title="Key:disused">disused</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:disused%3Dyes" title="Tag:disused=yes" class="mw-redirect">yes</a></tt> for alternative tagging.
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-railway_disused.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-railway disused.png" src="/w/images/thumb/e/eb/Rendering-railway_disused.png/100px-Rendering-railway_disused.png" width="100" height="80" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/eb/Rendering-railway_disused.png/150px-Rendering-railway_disused.png 1.5x, /w/images/e/eb/Rendering-railway_disused.png 2x" /></a>

<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dfunicular" title="Tag:railway=funicular"> funicular</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Cable driven inclined railways. In many cases they serve touristic interest, giving easy access to spectacular mountain views.
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering_funicular.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Rendering funicular.jpg" src="/w/images/8/8b/Rendering_funicular.jpg" width="92" height="82" /></a>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Vilnius_funicular.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Vilnius funicular.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/d/d8/Vilnius_funicular.jpg/80px-Vilnius_funicular.jpg" width="80" height="107" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/d8/Vilnius_funicular.jpg/120px-Vilnius_funicular.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d8/Vilnius_funicular.jpg/160px-Vilnius_funicular.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dlight_rail" title="Tag:railway=light rail"> light_rail</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A higher-standard tram system, normally in its own right-of-way. Often it connects towns and thus reaches a considerable length (tens of kilometer).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Pittsburgh LRT 4305 47L Gateway to Library April 2008.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/06/Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg/100px-Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg" width="100" height="66" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/06/Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg/150px-Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/06/Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg/200px-Pittsburgh_LRT_4305_47L_Gateway_to_Library_April_2008.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dminiature" title="Tag:railway=miniature"> miniature</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Ridable_miniature_railway" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:en:Ridable miniature railway">Miniature railways</a> are narrower than narrow gauge and carry passengers.  They can be found in parks.
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Mini-railway-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Mini-railway-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/0/0d/Mini-railway-mapnik.png" width="100" height="100" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg" class="image"><img alt="3871553552 f2204c3d83 o.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/1c/3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg/100px-3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg" width="100" height="67" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/1c/3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg/150px-3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/1c/3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg/200px-3871553552_f2204c3d83_o.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dmonorail" title="Tag:railway=monorail"> monorail</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A railway with only a single rail. A monorail can run above the rail like in Las Vegas and Disneyland or can suspend below the rail like the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wuppertal_Schwebebahn" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:en:Wuppertal Schwebebahn">Wuppertal Schwebebahn</a> (Germany)
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Kl_monorail.jpg" class="image" title="Monorail in Kuala Lumpur"><img alt="Monorail in Kuala Lumpur" src="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Kl_monorail.jpg/100px-Kl_monorail.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/07/Kl_monorail.jpg/150px-Kl_monorail.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/07/Kl_monorail.jpg/200px-Kl_monorail.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dnarrow_gauge" title="Tag:railway=narrow gauge"> narrow_gauge</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Narrow-gauge passenger or freight trains. Narrow gauge railways can have mainline railway service like the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhaetian_Railway" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Rhaetian Railway">Rhaetian Railway</a> in Switzerland or can be a small light industrial railway. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:gauge" title="Key:gauge">gauge</a>=*</tt> to specify the actual width of rails.
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering_narrow_gauge.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Rendering narrow gauge.jpg" src="/w/images/5/56/Rendering_narrow_gauge.jpg" width="110" height="106" /></a>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Narrow_gauge.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Narrow gauge.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/7/73/Narrow_gauge.jpg/80px-Narrow_gauge.jpg" width="80" height="107" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/73/Narrow_gauge.jpg/120px-Narrow_gauge.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/73/Narrow_gauge.jpg/160px-Narrow_gauge.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dpreserved" title="Tag:railway=preserved"> preserved</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A railway running historic trains, usually a tourist attraction (changed to preserved from preserved_rail as "rail" is redundant).

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>

</td>

</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:bridge" title="Key:bridge"> bridge</a>

<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> If the railway goes over a street, waterway or other railway.
</td>

<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:electrified" title="Key:electrified"> electrified</a>
</td>
<td> contact_line / rail / yes / no
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> contact_line: a power line over the train head<br /> rail: a third rail near the track supplying the train with power<br /> yes: electrified track, but no details available<br /> no: track with no power supply
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Overhead_power_lines.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Overhead power lines.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c4/Overhead_power_lines.jpg/100px-Overhead_power_lines.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c4/Overhead_power_lines.jpg/150px-Overhead_power_lines.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c4/Overhead_power_lines.jpg/200px-Overhead_power_lines.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:embankment" title="Key:embankment"> embankment</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>

</td>
<td> A section where the railway is raised significantly higher than ground level
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Railway_embankment.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Railway embankment.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/2/25/Railway_embankment.jpg/80px-Railway_embankment.jpg" width="80" height="107" srcset="/w/images/thumb/2/25/Railway_embankment.jpg/120px-Railway_embankment.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/2/25/Railway_embankment.jpg/160px-Railway_embankment.jpg 2x" /></a>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:frequency" title="Key:frequency"> frequency</a>
</td>
<td> number [kHz/MHz/GHz]
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The frequency with which a line is electrified. Use 0 for DC. Also see the voltage tag.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Relatively short lengths of track, built to give one company or entity access to a main or branch line.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:service" title="Key:service"> service</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:service%3Dyard" title="Tag:service=yard"> yard</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Tracks within railway company operated marshaling or maintenance yards
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:tracks" title="Key:tracks"> tracks</a>
</td>
<td> number
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Number of parallel tracks in close proximity when mapped as a single way. If not given means <i>unknown</i> and defaults to 1. In many parts of the world the tracks are being drawn out separately so that there is more detail, in which case this tag isn't used.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:tunnel" title="Key:tunnel"> tunnel</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> If the railway goes below ground. Should be always present on subways.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Haywards Heath tunnel.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/7/72/Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg/100px-Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/72/Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg/150px-Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/72/Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg/200px-Haywards_Heath_tunnel.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:usage" title="Key:usage"> usage</a>
</td>
<td> main / branch / freight / industrial / military / tourism
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td>
<p>main line: heavy traffic <br />
branch line: connecting places with a mainline <br />
freight: freight service only <br />
industrial:  servicing large plants (iron, chemical etc.), surface mining, ... <br />
military: servicing military area <br />
tourism: most mountain rails (rack-rails, funicular) and preserved railways. 
</p>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:voltage" title="Key:voltage"> voltage</a>
</td>
<td> number
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The voltage with which a line is electrified. Also see the frequency tag.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> <a href="/wiki/Railway_stations" title="Railway stations">Stations</a> and Stops
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dhalt" title="Tag:railway=halt"> halt</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A small station, may not have a platform, trains may only stop on request.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png" class="image"><img alt="Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png" src="/w/images/thumb/2/2e/Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png/100px-Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="/w/images/thumb/2/2e/Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png/150px-Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png 1.5x, /w/images/2/2e/Mapping-Features-Tram-With-Halt.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Railway_halt.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Railway halt.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/4/4b/Railway_halt.jpg/80px-Railway_halt.jpg" width="80" height="68" srcset="/w/images/thumb/4/4b/Railway_halt.jpg/120px-Railway_halt.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/4/4b/Railway_halt.jpg/160px-Railway_halt.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:public_transport" title="Key:public transport"> public_transport</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:public_transport%3Dplatform" title="Tag:public transport=platform"> platform</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> This is parallel to the rail line for showing where the actual platforms are. It is also to know where you can change platform and enter the station, so use footpaths to connect them. This is really useful for routing too.
</td>
<td>
</td>

</td></tr>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>

<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Stootblok_(staal).jpg" class="image"><img alt="Stootblok (staal).jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/a/a8/Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg/100px-Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/a/a8/Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg/150px-Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/a/a8/Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg/200px-Stootblok_%28staal%29.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:railway" title="Key:railway"> railway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:railway%3Dderail" title="Tag:railway=derail"> derail</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> a device used to prevent fouling of a rail track by unauthorized movements of trains or unattended rolling stock. See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derail_(railroad)" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Derail (railroad)">Derail_(railroad)</a>
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Route">Route</span></h3>
<p>Used to describe routes of many kinds. See also <a href="/wiki/Relation:route" title="Relation:route">Relation:route</a>.
</p>

<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This table is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:route" title="Template:Map Features:route">Editable here</a>.</span>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Shop">Shop</span></h3>
<p>A shop is a place of business stocked with goods for sale. See <a href="/wiki/Shops" title="Shops">Shops</a> for more details.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

Alternatively you can use the more versatile <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:organic" title="Key:organic">organic</a>=*</tt> in combination with a general <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:shop" title="Key:shop">shop</a>=*</tt> key (In this case: <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:shop" title="Key:shop">shop</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:shop%3Dsupermarket" title="Tag:shop=supermarket">supermarket</a></tt> or <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:shop" title="Key:shop">shop</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:shop%3Dconvenience" title="Tag:shop=convenience">convenience</a></tt>).

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A shop that sells fabric and other materials for the purpose of making clothes and other products, eg dress making.

<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Discount_store.2C_charity">Discount store, charity</span></h4>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:shop" title="Key:shop"> shop</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:shop%3Dcharity" title="Tag:shop=charity"> charity</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>

</td>

</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:shop" title="Key:shop"> shop</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:shop%3Dvacant" title="Tag:shop=vacant"> vacant</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Don't use this anymore - a vacancy is not a shop and should not show up on maps as a shop. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:disused:shop" title="Key:disused:shop" class="mw-redirect">disused:shop</a>=*</tt> instead. Not deleting a shop that has been closed can be useful to avoid confusing other mappers who may not know about this (please leave a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:note" title="Key:note">note</a>=*</tt>). Then you can keep the corresponding object and simply edit it when a new shop opens on the same spot.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Sport">Sport</span></h3>
<p>Use to provide information about which sports are placed on a facility such as a pitch or stadium. Use in conjunction with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:landuse" title="Key:landuse">landuse</a>=*</tt> or <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:leisure" title="Key:leisure">leisure</a>=*</tt>.
</p>
