<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:sport%3Dboules" title="Tag:sport=boules"> boules</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A collective name for games played with metal balls, popular in France (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boules" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Boules">on Wikipedia</a>).
<p>The different variations of this sport can be specified by also adding a <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:type" title="Key:type">type</a>=*</tt> tag. Values for this <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:type" title="Key:type">type</a>=*</tt> tag are e.g.: petanque, lyonnaise, extreme, ... 
</p>
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A game played between 2 or more players on a small grass pitch hitting wooden or plastic balls with a mallet through hoops embedded into the grass. (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/croquet" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:croquet">on Wikipedia</a>)
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:sport%3Dequestrian" title="Tag:sport=equestrian"> equestrian</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Equestrianism, sports involving the skill of riding or driving horses (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equestrianism" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Equestrianism">on Wikipedia</a>).
<p>Often associated internationally with show jumping and dressage, but also including endurance riding, eventing, reining, tent pegging, vaulting, polo, horse racing, driving, rodeo and more.
</p><p>See also <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:sport" title="Key:sport">sport</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:sport%3Dhorse_racing" title="Tag:sport=horse racing">horse_racing</a></tt>
</p>
</td>
<td>
</td>

</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Association football, more commonly known as football or soccer, a team sport played between two teams of eleven players (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/soccer" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:soccer">on Wikipedia</a>). Note: While called "football" (fussball, fotball, ...) in many countries, it is best to tag it as "soccer" to avoid confusion with other usages of <a href="/wiki/Football" title="Football">"football"</a>
</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Tourism">Tourism</span></h3>
<p>Used to map places and things of specific interest to tourists: places to see, places to stay, things and places providing support. See <a href="/wiki/Key:tourism" title="Key:tourism">Key:tourism</a> for more information. See <a href="/wiki/Tourism" title="Tourism">Tourism</a> for a general introduction.
</p>

</th>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:tourism%3Dguest_house" title="Tag:tourism=guest house"> guest_house</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_node.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf node.png" src="/w/images/b/b5/Mf_node.png" width="20" height="20" /></a> <a href="/wiki/File:Mf_area.png" class="image"><img alt="Mf area.png" src="/w/images/8/83/Mf_area.png" width="20" height="20" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guest_house" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Guest house">Guest house</a>. Accommodation without hotel license that is typically owner-operated, offers a room and breakfast with staff not available 24/7, ranging from purpose-built guest houses to family-based Bed&amp;Breakfast.
</td>

<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This table is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:tourism" title="Template:Map Features:tourism">Editable here</a>.</span>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Waterway">Waterway</span></h3>
<p>In all rivers, canals etc., the way should be aligned in the direction of water flow. See <a href="/wiki/Waterways" title="Waterways">Waterways</a> for an introduction to the mapping of waterways.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th class="unsortable"> Comment
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> natural watercourses
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Driver" title="Tag:waterway=river"> river</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> For narrow rivers which will be rendered as a line.  For larger rivers (defined as more than 12m across) see <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway">waterway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Driverbank" title="Tag:waterway=riverbank">riverbank</a></tt> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.omegawiki.org/DefinedMeaning:river_(3253)">Other languages</a>).
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-waterway-river.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-waterway-river.png" src="/w/images/3/31/Rendering-waterway-river.png" width="96" height="69" /></a>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Nau im Langenauer Ried 600x450.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/9/98/Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg/80px-Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/98/Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg/120px-Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/98/Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg/160px-Nau_im_Langenauer_Ried_600x450.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Driverbank" title="Tag:waterway=riverbank"> riverbank</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Used for larger rivers, to define an area between the opposite riverbanks. See <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:water" title="Key:water">water</a>=river</tt> for alternative tagging.
</td>
<td>  <a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-waterway-riverbank.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-waterway-riverbank.png" src="/w/images/c/cc/Rendering-waterway-riverbank.png" width="96" height="77" /></a>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Dscf1891-800.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Dscf1891-800.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/f/f5/Dscf1891-800.jpg/80px-Dscf1891-800.jpg" width="80" height="60" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/f5/Dscf1891-800.jpg/120px-Dscf1891-800.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/f/f5/Dscf1891-800.jpg/160px-Dscf1891-800.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dstream" title="Tag:waterway=stream"> stream</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A naturally-formed waterway that is too thin to be classed as a river. An active, able-bodied person should be able to jump over it if trees along it aren't too thick.
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3f/Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png/80px-Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png" width="80" height="74" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3f/Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png/120px-Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3f/Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png/160px-Rendering-waterway-stream-mapnik.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg" class="image"><img alt="450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/f/fe/450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg/80px-450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg" width="80" height="78" srcset="/w/images/thumb/f/fe/450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg/120px-450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/f/fe/450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg/160px-450px-Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dwadi" title="Tag:waterway=wadi"> wadi</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A natural, dry (ephemeral) riverbed that contains water only during times of heavy rain or simply an intermittent stream, in semi-arid areas. Also known as a "Wash" in the deserts of America.
</td>
<td>  <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png" class="image"><img alt="Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ec/Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png/80px-Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png" width="80" height="79" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ec/Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png/120px-Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ec/Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png/160px-Rendering-waterway-wadi-mapnik.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:NahalashanS.jpg" class="image"><img alt="NahalashanS.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c1/NahalashanS.jpg/80px-NahalashanS.jpg" width="80" height="52" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c1/NahalashanS.jpg/120px-NahalashanS.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c1/NahalashanS.jpg/160px-NahalashanS.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>

<th colspan="6"> barriers on waterways
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Ddam" title="Tag:waterway=dam"> dam</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A wall built across a river or stream to impound the water. A dam normally does not have water flowing over the top of it.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Amagase_Dam.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Amagase Dam.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/7/77/Amagase_Dam.jpg/80px-Amagase_Dam.jpg" width="80" height="53" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/77/Amagase_Dam.jpg/120px-Amagase_Dam.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/77/Amagase_Dam.jpg/160px-Amagase_Dam.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dweir" title="Tag:waterway=weir"> weir</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A barrier built across a river, sometimes to divert water for industrial purposes. Water can still flow over the top.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Alifakovac Miljacka.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3c/Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg/80px-Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg" width="80" height="64" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3c/Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg/120px-Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3c/Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg/160px-Alifakovac_Miljacka.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dlock_gate" title="Tag:waterway=lock gate"> lock_gate</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> To mark the position of gates at each end of a lock. Alternatively, for smaller locks use a single <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:lock" title="Key:lock">lock</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:lock%3Dyes" title="Tag:lock=yes" class="mw-redirect">yes</a></tt> node in the middle of the lock.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" class="image"><img alt="JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/80px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" width="80" height="59" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/120px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/160px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> other features on waterways
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dturning_point" title="Tag:waterway=turning point"> turning_point</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A place to turn the driving direction for vessels, where the boats are longer than the river/canal is wide. Use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:maxlength" title="Key:maxlength">maxlength</a>=*</tt> to denote the maximum length of the vessel.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway"> waterway</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dwater_point" title="Tag:waterway=water point"> water_point</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> This tag is for ports/marinas where you can get large amounts of potable water.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> Some additional attributes for waterways
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:intermittent" title="Key:intermittent"> intermittent</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Indicates that the waterway does not have a permanent flow (i.e. is sometimes/often dry).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:lock" title="Key:lock"> lock</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> (<a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>)
</td>
<td> A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Lock_(water_transport)" class="extiw" title="w:en:Lock (water transport)">lock</a> is used for moving boats between waterways at two different levels. Can tag either the section of the way between the gates (detailed) or just a single node in the waterway (less detailed).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" class="image"><img alt="JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/80px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg" width="80" height="59" srcset="/w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/120px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/c/c7/JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg/160px-JesusGreenLock-Cambridge.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:mooring" title="Key:mooring"> mooring</a>
</td>
<td> yes/private/no
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A length of bank where boats are explicitly permitted to moor. <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:maxstay" title="Key:maxstay">maxstay</a>=*</tt> should be used for timing information.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Lamanage La Rochelle.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/03/Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg/80px-Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg" width="80" height="49" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/03/Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg/120px-Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/03/Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg/160px-Lamanage_La_Rochelle.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:service" title="Key:service"> service</a>
</td>
<td> transportation/water_power/irrigation
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:waterway" title="Key:waterway">waterway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Dcanal" title="Tag:waterway=canal">canal</a></tt> may have one (or more; separate with semicolons) uses.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:tunnel" title="Key:tunnel"> tunnel</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Tag:tunnel%3Dculvert" title="Tag:tunnel=culvert"> culvert</a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> (<a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>)
</td>
<td> For a stream passing under a road use <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:tunnel" title="Key:tunnel">tunnel</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:tunnel%3Dculvert" title="Tag:tunnel=culvert">culvert</a></tt> on the section of stream passing under the road (don't use this tag for open-top culverts or roads using the culvert structure as a bridge (<tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:bridge" title="Key:bridge">bridge</a>=<a href="/w/index.php?title=Tag:bridge%3Dculvert&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Tag:bridge=culvert (page does not exist)">culvert</a></tt>)).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Culvert.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Culvert.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/0/00/Culvert.jpg/80px-Culvert.jpg" width="80" height="53" srcset="/w/images/thumb/0/00/Culvert.jpg/120px-Culvert.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/0/00/Culvert.jpg/160px-Culvert.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Additional_properties">Additional properties</span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Addresses">Addresses</span></h3>
<p>Used to provide postal information for the building or facility. See <a href="/wiki/Addresses" title="Addresses">Addresses</a> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr" title="Key:addr">addr</a>=*</tt> for more details on usage.
</p>
<table class="wikitable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th> Comment
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="6"> Tags for individual houses
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:housenumber" title="Key:addr:housenumber" class="mw-redirect"> addr:housenumber</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_numbering" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:House numbering">house number</a> (may contain letters, dashes or other characters).<br /><a href="/wiki/Addresses" title="Addresses">Addresses</a> describes ways to tag a single building with multiple addresses.<br /> Please do not only tag <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:housenumber" title="Key:addr:housenumber" class="mw-redirect">addr:housenumber</a>=*</tt>, but also add at least <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:street" title="Key:addr:street" class="mw-redirect">addr:street</a>=*</tt> (or map the belonging to a street with a relation using <a href="/wiki/Relation:associatedStreet" title="Relation:associatedStreet">associatedStreet relation</a>).
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Wien Lainzer Str 8a.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/7/77/Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg/100px-Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg" width="100" height="70" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/77/Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg/150px-Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/77/Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg/200px-Wien_Lainzer_Str_8a.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:housename" title="Key:addr:housename" class="mw-redirect"> addr:housename</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The name of a house. <br />This is sometimes used in some countries like England instead of (or in addition to) a house number.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:street" title="Key:addr:street" class="mw-redirect"> addr:street</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The (main) name of the respective street. <br />A way with <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=*</tt> and the corresponding name should be found nearby. The belonging to a street can alternatively be represented by a <a href="/wiki/Relation:associatedStreet" title="Relation:associatedStreet">associatedStreet relation</a>. The keys <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:housenumber" title="Key:addr:housenumber" class="mw-redirect">addr:housenumber</a>=*</tt> und <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:street" title="Key:addr:street" class="mw-redirect">addr:street</a>=*</tt> in principle are the only necessary ones if there are valid border polygons. If you are not sure if it is so, just add <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:city" title="Key:addr:city" class="mw-redirect">addr:city</a>=*</tt>, <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:postcode" title="Key:addr:postcode" class="mw-redirect">addr:postcode</a>=*</tt> and <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:addr:country" title="Key:addr:country" class="mw-redirect">addr:country</a>=*</tt>. This is usually.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Kirkland,_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Kirkland, WA - double street sign.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/5/54/Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg/100px-Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg" width="100" height="65" srcset="/w/images/thumb/5/54/Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg/150px-Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/5/54/Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg/200px-Kirkland%2C_WA_-_double_street_sign.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:place" title="Key:addr:place"> addr:place</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> part of address, which is not related to street, but to some territorial zone, linear object, node or some abstract object.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Postal_code" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Postal code">postal code</a> of the building/area.
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:city" title="Key:addr:city" class="mw-redirect"> addr:city</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> May or may not be a clone of <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:is_in:city" title="Key:is in:city" class="mw-redirect">is_in:city</a>=*</tt> (in some places the city in the address corresponds to the post office that serves the area rather than the actual city, if any, in which the building is located)! The name of the city as given in postal addresses of the building/area.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Lillerod.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Lillerod.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/1/18/Lillerod.jpg/100px-Lillerod.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/1/18/Lillerod.jpg/150px-Lillerod.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/1/18/Lillerod.jpg/200px-Lillerod.jpg 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:country" title="Key:addr:country" class="mw-redirect"> addr:country</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:ISO_3166-1_alpha-2" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:en:ISO 3166-1 alpha-2">ISO 3166-1 alpha-2</a> two letter country code in <i>upper case</i>. <br />Example: "DE" for Germany, "FR" for France, "IT" for Italy. <br /><i>Caveat: The ISO 3166-1 code for Great Britain is "<b>GB</b>" and not "UK".</i>. See also:  <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:is_in:country" title="Key:is in:country" class="mw-redirect">is_in:country</a>=*</tt>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:addr:full" title="Key:addr:full" class="mw-redirect"> addr:full</a>
</td>
<td> user defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Use this for a full-text, often multi-line, address if you find the structured address fields unsuitable for denoting the address of this particular location. Examples: "Fifth house on the left after the village oak, Smalltown, Smallcountry" or "1200 West Sunset Boulevard Suite 110A". Beware that these strings can hardly be parsed by software.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>

</td>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Name">Name</span></h3>
<p>The name tag is the primary tag used for naming a Element. See <a href="/wiki/Names" title="Names">Names</a> for more information on how to use this tag.
</p>
<table class="wikitable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th> Comment
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:name" title="Key:name"> name</a>
</td>
<td> User Defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> The common default name. (Note: For disputed areas, please use the name as displayed on e.g. street signs for the name tag. Put all alternatives into either localized name tags (e.g. name:tr/name:el) or the variants (e.g. loc_name/old_name/alt_name). Thank you.)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:name" title="Key:name"> name:<i>&lt;lg&gt;</i></a>
</td>
<td> User Defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Name in different <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes">language</a> eg. name:fr=Londres. See: <a href="/wiki/Multilingual_names" title="Multilingual names">Multilingual names</a>
</td></tr>

</td>
<td> User Defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:name" title="Key:name"> sorting_name</a>
</td>
<td> User Defined
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> name, used for correct sorting of names — This is only needed when sorting names cannot be based only on their orthography (using the Unicode Collation Algorithm with collation tables tailored by language and script, or when sorted lists of names are including names written in multiple languages and/or scripts) but requires ignoring some parts such as:
<ul>
<li> ignoring leading articles, or
</li>
<li> lowering the relative importance of first names cited before a last name,
</li>
<li> ignoring the generic part of a street name when it occurs before the specific name (e.g. in French with "rue", "boulevard", "place", etc.),
</li>
</ul>
<p>all of them being ignored at the primary sort level and not easily inferable by a preprocessing algorithm.
</p>
</td></tr></table>
<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This table is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:name" title="Template:Map Features:name">Editable here</a>.</span>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Properties">Properties</span></h3>
<p>Used to give additional information of a general nature about another element.
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th class="unsortable"> Comment
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th class="unsortable" style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:area" title="Key:area"> area</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Means a feature that is normally linear is an area. You should not add this to features that are already defined as an area type.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:bridge" title="Key:bridge"> bridge</a>
</td>
<td> yes / aqueduct / viaduct / swing / ...
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A bridge, use together with the layer tag. Value "yes" is generic, or you can specialize.
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png" class="image"><img alt="Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png" src="/w/images/thumb/9/9a/Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png/100px-Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png" width="100" height="85" srcset="/w/images/thumb/9/9a/Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png/150px-Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/9/9a/Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png/200px-Mapping-Features-Road-Bridge.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Bridge-yes.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Bridge-yes.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/8/84/Bridge-yes.jpg/100px-Bridge-yes.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="/w/images/thumb/8/84/Bridge-yes.jpg/150px-Bridge-yes.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/8/84/Bridge-yes.jpg/200px-Bridge-yes.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:covered" title="Key:covered"> covered</a>
</td>
<td> yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a><a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a><a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td>  Used to denote that a node, way or area is covered by another entity (or in some cases the ground), when the use of layers is inappropriate, or additional clarification is needed.
</td>
<td>  Various, depending on the covered entity
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/File:Covered.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Covered.jpg" src="/w/images/thumb/d/dc/Covered.jpg/100px-Covered.jpg" width="100" height="74" srcset="/w/images/thumb/d/dc/Covered.jpg/150px-Covered.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/dc/Covered.jpg/200px-Covered.jpg 2x" /></a>
</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:ele" title="Key:ele"> ele</a>
</td>
<td> Number
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Elevation (also known as altitude or height) above <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sea_level" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Sea level">mean sea level</a> in metre, based on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geoid" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Geoid">geoid</a> model <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EGM96" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:EGM96">EGM 96</a> which is used by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WGS84" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:WGS84">WGS 84</a> (<a href="/wiki/GPS" title="GPS">GPS</a>). (see also <a href="/wiki/Altitude" title="Altitude">Altitude</a>)
</td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:layer" title="Key:layer">layer</a>

<td> -5 to 5

</td>
<td> 0: ground (default); -1..-5:under ground layer; 1..5 (not +1):above ground layer<br />This is intended to indicate actual physical separation, shouldn't be used just to influence rendering order.

<td> yes

<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> A tunnel, use together with the layer tag.

</td></tr>

Makes most sense when applied to areas.
</td>

<td><a href="/wiki/Elements#Node" title="Node"><img alt="Node" src="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/20px-Osm_element_node.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/30px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/7/76/Osm_element_node.svg/40px-Osm_element_node.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Area_.28closed_way_.29" title="Area"><img alt="Area" src="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/20px-Osm_element_area.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/30px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/e6/Osm_element_area.svg/40px-Osm_element_area.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> To record the URI, source reference (eg Landsat) or other link to physical sources.
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr></table>
<p><span style="font-size:80%;line-height:120%">This table is a wiki template with a default description in English. <a href="/wiki/Template:Map_Features:references" title="Template:Map Features:references">Editable here</a>.</span>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Restrictions">Restrictions</span></h3>
<p>Used to define restrictions that apply to the associated element. For more information see <a href="/wiki/Restrictions" title="Restrictions">Restrictions</a>.
</p>
<table class="wikitable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" width="100%">

<tr style="background-color:#F8F4C2">
<th style="width:70px"> Key
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Value
</th>
<th style="width:70px"> Element
</th>
<th> Comment
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Rendering
</th>
<th style="width:100px"> Photo
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="7"> Vehicle types
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:access" title="Key:access"> access</a>
</td>
<td>  agricultural / delivery / designated / destination / forestry / no / official / permissive / private / unknown / yes
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> General access permission.
<ul>
<li><i>agricultural</i> - Only for agricultural traffic 
</li>
<li><i>delivery</i> - Only when delivering to the element. 
</li>
<li><i>designated</i> - A preferred or designated route for a specific vehicle type or types. Not compulsory but often marked by a traffic sign 
</li>
<li><i>destination</i> - Used for ways in designated local traffic areas, where traffic should only enter if its destination is within the area
</li>
<li><i>forestry</i> - Only for forestry traffic 
</li>
<li><i>no</i> - No access for the general public. Consider using another tag indicating who can use the element 
</li>
<li><i>official</i> - The way is dedicated to a specific mode of travel by law. Usually marked by traffic signs and exclusive. In Germany use is also compulsory. clarification needed
</li>
<li><i>permissive</i> - Open to general traffic until such time as the owner revokes the permission which they are legally allowed to do at any time in the future. 
</li>
<li><i>private</i> - Only with permission of the owner on an individual basis 
</li>
<li><i>unknown</i> - No information provided on access. This is the default value for most features with a general assumption that access is allowed for all purposes 
</li>
<li><i>yes</i> - The public has an official, legal right of access, i.e. it's a right of way  (default value)
</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:access" title="Key:access"> agricultural</a>

</td>
<td> Access permission for agricultural vehicles, e.g. tractors.
</td>

</td></tr>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:access" title="Key:access"> bicycle</a>
</td>
<td>  yes / designated / official / private / permissive / dismount / destination / delivery / agricultural / forestry / unknown / no
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> Access permission for bicycles. For values see above. Usage of bicycle=dismount and bicycle=no will vary in different countries. If according to local traffic rules a bicycle is no longer seen as a bicycle when there's no one driving it, then there's no need for using bicycle=dismount. If the local legislation still sees an undriven bicycle as a bicycle then you may need to use both bicycle=dismount and bicycle=no.
</td>
<td>

<td> <a href="/wiki/Key:oneway" title="Key:oneway"> oneway</a>
</td>
<td> yes / no / -1
</td>
<td> <a href="/wiki/Elements#Way" title="Way"><img alt="Way" src="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/20px-Osm_element_way.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="/w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/30px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/e/ee/Osm_element_way.svg/40px-Osm_element_way.svg.png 2x" /></a>
</td>
<td> <br /><tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:oneway" title="Key:oneway">oneway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:oneway%3Dyes" title="Tag:oneway=yes" class="mw-redirect">yes</a></tt> for traffic direction same as the sequence of nodes of the way (<a href="/wiki/Maplint" title="Maplint">maplint</a> will highlight "true" and "1", so they can be updated to "yes").<br /><tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:oneway" title="Key:oneway">oneway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:oneway%3Dno" title="Tag:oneway=no" class="mw-redirect">no</a></tt> for bidirectional traffic (<a href="/wiki/Maplint" title="Maplint">maplint</a> will highlight "false" and "0", so they can be updated to "no").<br /><tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:oneway" title="Key:oneway">oneway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:oneway%3D-1" title="Tag:oneway=-1" class="mw-redirect">-1</a></tt> for traffic direction opposite to the sequence of nodes of the way (if the way cannot be reversed).
<p>Some road types are assumed to be one-way (e.g. <tt style="background-color:#e0e0f0; white-space:pre;" dir="ltr"><a href="/wiki/Key:highway" title="Key:highway">highway</a>=<a href="/wiki/Tag:highway%3Dmotorway" title="Tag:highway=motorway">motorway</a></tt>), others are assumed to be two-way (most others).  The  direction of the sequence of nodes of a way is indicated by sequential order of nodes within the way. <br />Hint: When using the editor JOSM, enable 'arrows'!). 
</p><p>The maplint highlighting will help with updating of the tags which will allow simplification of style sheets to prevent unintentional rendering errors creeping in. See <a href="/wiki/Talk:Key:oneway" title="Talk:Key:oneway">Talk:Key:oneway</a>. 
</p>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td> <div class="center"><div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:OneWaySign.png" class="image"><img alt="OneWaySign.png" src="/w/images/thumb/3/3d/OneWaySign.png/35px-OneWaySign.png" width="35" height="35" srcset="/w/images/thumb/3/3d/OneWaySign.png/53px-OneWaySign.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/3/3d/OneWaySign.png/70px-OneWaySign.png 2x" /></a></div></div>
</td></tr>
